quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,36,"Only those who listen will respond. As for the dead<sup>9</sup>, Allah will resurrect them, then to Him they will be returned.","[9] i.e., the dead of heart, meaning the disbelievers."
  6,37,"They say, “Why has no sign been sent down to him from his Lord?” Say, “Allah is Capable to send down a sign,” but most of them do not know [the consequences].",""
  6,38,"There is no moving creature on earth or a bird flying with its two wings, but are communities like you. We have missed nothing in the Record<sup>10</sup>, then to their Lord they will be gathered.","[10] i.e., the Preserved Tablet."
  6,39,"Those who reject Our verses are deaf and dumb in the depths of darkness. Whomever Allah wills, He causes him to stray and whomever He wills, He leads him to a straight path.",""
  6,40,"Say, “What do you think<sup>11</sup>, if there comes upon you the punishment of Allah or the Hour comes upon you, would you then call upon anyone other than Allah, if you are truthful?”","[11] i.e., “Tell me..."""
  6,41,"No, it is Him alone you would call upon<sup>12</sup>. If He willed, He could remove whatever harm made you call upon Him, and you would forget whatever partners you associate with Him.”","[12] When you are touched by hardship."
  6,42,"We sent messengers to nations before you and seized them with poverty and hardship, so that they may humble themselves.",""
  6,43,"If only they had humbled themselves when Our affliction came upon them, but their hearts were hardened, and Satan made their misdeeds appealing to them.",""
  6,44,"When they forgot the reminder that they were given<sup>13</sup>, We opened for them the doors of everything – until when they rejoiced in pride for what they were given, We seized them by surprise, so they fell into utter despair.","[13] i.e., their trial by hardship or the warning of their prophets."
